reviews.text:
This is my first time at the Saratoga Springs location, and I had a great experience.

I went through the drive-through, which was super quick and easy. The lady at the window was super helpful and nice.

They gave plenty of sauce without me, even having to ask.

I got some rice, beans and for al pastor tacos, which was all delicious!

Food was great. I got the super bowl with Asada and Chicken. It was a huge serving for just $10. Great rice, beans, and meat. I liked the asada the most, the chicken was kinda dry but seasoned well. Also got a medium horchata and it was bomb!

In my humble opinion, Don Joaquin is the best Mexican restaurant around here. Consistency in quality and customer service. Everyone there is so very nice and professional. Y‚Äôall are doing God‚Äôs work. Incredible great prices too. Thank you. I will always be a loyal customer. ‚ù§Ô∏è

I came to eat later in the evening. First time here. Absolutely amazing Asada Fries. Best I've ever had and for like $11! Fresh AF, amazing fresh gaucamole salsa at the salsa bar, crunchy perfectly crispy fries, so much flavor! Fed hungry ole me just fine! I can't wait to come back and try everything else! I noticed ppl saying confusion about order numbers, but it seems like they implemented beeping order coasters! Much better. Love the atmosphere as well! üëå

I loved this place in Provo and the quality seems the same here in Saratoga Springs. I especially like the taco Tuesday deal, but unfortunately that didn‚Äôt cover the carnitas taco I got. My favorites were their asada and pastor. Good selection of salsas that had a pretty good kick. The food came out quick.

detailedReviews.author: Robert Smith
detailedReviews.text:
Disappointed!
The food had no flavor.
I brought my family to try it out as we‚Äôve been eyeing this place for quite a while. I love Mexican food! I‚Äôm not even that picky, but I ordered the green burrito with asada, while my kids ordered the breakfast burritos with sausage. The chorizo was flavorless was the first thing I heard from the boys. I took a bite thinking chorizo couldn‚Äôt be flavorless, but it was bad. I definitely wouldn‚Äôt order that again. Beto‚Äôs breakfast burritos are SO MUCH BETTER!
As I was eating my burrito that didn‚Äôt have much flavor either I pulled a very large piece of fat out of it. I like fat, but give me a break, it was huge. Very disappointing!
I complained about it all, and if I were managing this place I would have offered a full refund. They said they credited my card back for the price of one burrito. I will not be returning and couldn‚Äôt be more disappointed.

detailedReviews.author: Izzy Smith
detailedReviews.text: We have wanted to try this place out for months and today was the day. Right off the service left a lot to be desired. But we stayed hopeful for good food. Nope. The chorizo had zero flavor- not sure how they managed that as it‚Äôs the most flavorful meat on a Mexican menu typically. Then to top off the experience there was a five inch slab  of fat tossed into the asada burrito.  The chicken green burrito and potatoes were good but we won‚Äôt be back.

detailedReviews.author: Mercedes Rojas
detailedReviews.text: I took my son for he's birthday here, I order a Jamica water (hibiscus water) a super bowl with chicken, stake rice and beans. The water was horrible it tastes rotten and it smelled disgusting, I saw one of the workers just adding new water to the old. I went up to them and said that my water was horrible they offered to change it but it still had the rotten taste to it do to the fact that they just add new water to the old. The meat on my bowl wasn't good overall a bad experience I dont recommend this place.

detailedReviews.author: Silas Wright
detailedReviews.text: CHECK WHAT THEY CHARGE BEFORE YOU BUY, THEY WILL OVERCHARGE THAN WHATS ADVERTISED! I thought the food was great, but what I didn't appreciate was that the deal price that was advertised was not what I was charged. When asked them about this, they said they only advertise cash prices (though they charged it before asking whether I was paying cash or card). It's legal to charge a different amount for cash and card, as long as they are clear on it. No where does it mention different prices or added charges for cards  Each taco was about 20% more than what was advertised. Small enough that I bet most people won't notice.

detailedReviews.text: Yesterday I came to eat and the restaurant was closed.   The sign on the door said that you were closed to support immigrants.
